* Thrown if the Java Virtual Machine or a {@code ClassLoader} instance * tries to load in the definition of a class (as part of a normal method call * or as part of creating a new instance using the {@code new} expression) * and no definition of the class could be found. *

* The searched-for class definition existed when the currently * executing class was compiled, but the definition can no longer be * found. * * @since 1.0
